720081f-a.text:
162 to 154 Grand Street, north side, west from Centre to Lafayette Streets, showing 2 old 27 -story houses (Nos. 162 and 160) at and adjoining the N.W. corner of Centre Street. On the right appears Nos. 231 and 233 Centre Street (two small frame houses with brick fronts), adjoining and north of the N.W. corner of Grand Street. Three of these views are similar; No. 4 shows a more extensive view northward on Centre Street. The 1925 Atlas shows a two story building on the sites of former Nos. 162, 160 and 158 Grand Street and Nos. 231, 233 and 235 Centre Street.
November 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
720081f-a.folder: Grand Street & Centre Street, Manhattan, NY
